Package seq_loop
-----------------------------------------------
Description: This package aims to accomplish the tasks in Assignment 2.3 of analyzing timing of communication between ROS2 nodes.
Requirements: matplotlib, pandas.

Building instructions: Place folder in src. Build normally via colcon build.

*****Node: seq05*****
Input:
/loop05_out
        Type: std_msgs/msg/UInt64
        The regurgitated message being receieved.

Output:
/seq05_out
        Type: std_msgs/msg/UInt64
        The original message being sent.
        
*****Node: loop05*****
Input:
/loop05_out
        Type: std_msgs/msg/UInt64
        The original message being received.

Output:
/seq05_out
        Type: std_msgs/msg/UInt64
        The message being regurgitated.
	
Run:
	ros2 launch seq_loop seq_loop.launch.py 
	# Output file is saved in the directory with the python file, it runs automatically after the test, if needed to run at any other time inside /scripts
	python3 plot_results.py
	# Change parameters during runtime 
	ros2 param set /seq05 depth 5

Parameters:
	reliability: [string] reliability policy used by QoS
	durability: [string] durability policy used by QoS
	history: [string] history policy used by QoS
	depth: [int] Length of buffer used by QoS, if history is "keep_last"
	
Core components: 
	loop05 - seq_callback(): Receives the original message and sends it back.
	seq05 - timer_callback(): Sends the original messages periodically.
	seq05 - loop_callback(): Saves the time when the regurgitated message was received.
	seq05 - postprocess(): Runs after the whole test, checks which messages were succesfully sent for a round trip, for all successful messages calculates jitter and simple statistics, prints these statistics and the IDs of lost messages, then saves the data in a file.
